ntennial to tackle women's issues of today and tomorrow.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aFeminismzNew York (State)xHistory. 0aWomenxPolitical activityzNew York (State)xHistory. 0aWomenzNew York (State)xSuffagexHistory. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aHistory : History. 4aNew York/Regional : New York/Regional. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh1 aDowley, Kathleen M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHochul, Kathy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLewis, Susan Ingalls, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aO'Sullivan, Meg Devlin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847970540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438479705423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438479705/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles